summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Case number PHEH2012US006886 is an initial spontaneous legal report received on 28 Mar 2012 via a consumer's attorney in form of a civil complaint (reference no: 12 CV 2254) and follow up received on 15 Aug 2012, 16 Aug 2012, 17 Aug 2012, 20 Aug 2012, 23 Aug 2012, 29 Aug 2012, 30 Aug 2012, 31 Aug 2012, 05 Sep 2012, 07 Sep 2012, 11 Sep 2012, 17 Sep 2012, 19 Sep 2012, 20 Sep 2012, 24 Sep 2012, 02 Oct 2012, 17 Oct 2012, 18 Oct 2010, 31 Oct 2012 and 07 Dec 2012 from a physician via a consumer's attorney inclusive medical records. This report refers to adult female patient. The patient had relevant medical history of stem cell therapy, renal fistula and caesarean section. The patient was on multiple concomitant medications. Patient's family history was updated. The patient was smoker and allergic to Augmentin. The patient received Aredia (disodium pamidronate) and Zometa (zoledronate) for multiple myeloma for an unspecific duration and at an unknown dose. On an unspecified date patient suffered from osteonecrosis of the jaw, pain, infection, disfigurement, physical injury, emotional distress, mental anguish and physical disability. On an unspecified date the patient underwent bone marrow transplant. Record dated 22 Aug 2001 stated that patient had breast tenderness. Record dated 30 Aug 2001 stated that patient had severe weakness, disorientation, anorexia, muscle cramps and back pain because of ruptured disc and recent salmonella gastroenteritis. Record dated 31 Aug 2001 stated that patient had generalized colitis and esophagitis. Record dated 15 Sep 2001 stated that patient had occasional sleep disorder. Record dated 18 Sep 2001 stated that the patient had nystagmus and hoarseness. Record dated 26 Oct 2001, noted that the patient had depression, hyperthyroidism, severe anxiety, tachycardia and mild proptosis. Record dated 13 Nov 2001, noted that the patient was diagnosed with insomnia, palpitations, grave's disease and irregular heartbeat. Same dated records mentioned that patient underwent tubal ligation (on an unspecified date). Ultrasound abdomen performed on 10 Dec 2001 revealed mild hepatomegaly, cholecystitis and mild gall bladder 0.4 cm polyp. Record further stated that patient had lytic lesions in thoracic spine, lumbar spine, sacrum and iliac bones. Patient underwent radioactive iodine for hyperthyroidism in Feb 2002. Record dated 15 Feb 2002, noted that the patient experienced tremor, leg pain, back pain and salmonella typhi infection. Record dated 09 Jun 2002 stated that the patient had dizziness and nausea. Record dated 25 Oct 2002, noted that the patient had impaired memory and fatigue. Record dated 23 Jan 2003, noted that the patient was diagnosed with ophthalmopathy, thyrotoxicosis, dyslipidemia and bilateral periorbital edema. Record dated 07 Mar 2003, noted that the patient was diagnosed with mild hallux valgus and bursitis. Records dated 27 Jun 2003 stated that the patient had dry eye syndrome, myopia, astigmatism and presbyopia. Record dated Dec 2003, noted that the patient experienced manic episode. Records dated 31 Dec 2003 stated that the patient had nasal septal deviation. Records dated 25 Jun 2004 stated that the patient had keratitis. Record dated 03 Aug 2004 noted gastro esophageal reflux disease, slight kidney impairment and anemia. Record dated 21 Oct 2004, noted that the patient had left knee pain, hip pain and plantar fasciitis. Record dated 29 Jul 2005 stated that the patient had lid retraction. Dental records dated 03 Oct 2005, noted that the patient had bone loss. Record further stated that patient underwent hormone replacement therapy and blood transfusion. Records dated 11 Oct 2005 stated that the patient had multiple lytic lesions in the cranium. Record dated 04 Nov 2005 stated that patient had porta cath. On an unspecified date in 2006 Zometa (zoledronate) was stopped. Record dated 13 Jan 2006 stated that patient had internal and external haemorrhoids. Record dated 23 Feb 2006 stated that patient had chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (COPD). Records dated 03 Mar 2006 stated that the patient had scarring and fibrosis within the eyelid. Record dated 13 Apr 2006 stated that patient had patient had hot flashes. Record dated 16 May 2006 stated that the patient had thickening of the gallbladder wall. Record dated 30 Jun 2006 stated that patient had low blood pressure typically 90/60, cholelithiasis and extensive cholesterolosis. X-ray performed on 10 Jan 2007 revealed old anterolateral fracture of the 9th, 10th and 11th ribs. Records dated 27 Apr 2007 stated that the patient had ocular hypertension. Record dated 25 Jul 2007 stated that patient had thyroid orbitopathy. Record dated 28 Aug 2007 stated that patient had other facial nerve disorder. Record dated 19 Sep 2007 stated that patient had venous insufficiency and underwent porta cath removal. Echocardiogram dated 17 Apr 2008 stated that the patient had trace mitral regurgitation (MR) and trace tricuspid regurgitation (TR). Record dated 26 Aug 2008 stated that the patient had hypothyroidism. Record dated 28 Aug 2008 noted that the patient had multiple lesions in bones. Record dated 17 Jan 2010 stated that patient had dysfunctions associated with sleep stages or arousal from sleep and snoring/ respiratory abnormality, bradycardia, post nasal drip and psychiatric disorder. Record dated 11 Mar 2010 stated that patient had shortness of breath, chronic renal insufficiency due to dehydration. Record further stated that the patient had strep throat, chest aching acute, hemoptysis, rigors, marked leukocytosis, sepsis secondary to pneumonia, hyponatremia, respiratory distress and hypokalemia and glucose 119 mg/dl. Record dated 13 Mar 2010 stated that patient had gait dysfunction. Record dated 14 Mar 2010 stated that the patient had mild degenerative disc disease, same date patient underwent X-ray chest revealed tiny right pleural effusion. Record dated 16 Mar 2010 stated that patient had nearly complete resolution of the lung infiltrate. Record dated 26 Mar 2010 stated that the patient developed plantar calcaneal spur and pneumonia. Record dated 08 Sep 2010 stated that patient had odynophagia and burning left flank pain. Record dated 14 Sep 2010 noted that the patient was hospitalised for multiple drug resistant pneumonia. Record dated 07 Oct 2010 stated that patient had dysphagia, barret esophagus, guide-wire assisted esophageal dilation. In Nov 2010, the patient underwent dental extraction. Record dated 27 Jan 2011, noted that the patient underwent implant placement. Record further stated that the patient had mononucleosis and easy bruising. undOn 28 Jan 2011 patient erwent insertion of peripherally inserted central venous catheter (PICC). Record further stated that patient had osteomyelitis of the jaw. Dental records dated 08 Apr 2011, noted that the patient was diagnosed with exposed bone and non-healing. Record dated 21 Jul 2011, noted that the patient's teeth were loose and also had plaque. The patient underwent the procedure of removal bone on mandible. The patient also had caries control. Record dated 28 Jul 2011, noted that the patient had white spot on the lingual aspect of the 1r molar. Dental record dated 01 Aug 2011, noted that the patient underwent debridement of tooth # 31. Dental record 01 Sep 2011, noted that the patient had severe pain at injection site and muscle soreness. Dental records dated 10 Nov 2011, noted that the patient had inflammation, bleeding and wound. Record dated 14 Mar 2012 stated that the patient had levoscoliosis and degenerative changes of the thoracic spine. Record dated 17 Apr 2012 stated that patient had rectocele. Patient underwent repair of rectocele on 20 Apr 2012. Record dated 24 Apr 2012 stated that patient had some vaginal bleeding. Dental records dated 08 Jun 2012, noted that the patient had ulceration in area of tooth # 30. Record dated 24 Aug 2012 stated that the patient had bipolar disorder which was treated with Abilify (aripiprazole) and Klonopin (clonazepam). On an unspecified date the patient had hypertension (HTN). Seriousness and causality of these events were not provided. The treatment duration for Aredia and Zometa was not provided. The outcome of the event salmonella typhi infection was resolved. The outcome of the events insomnia, tremor, back pain, impaired memory, lung infiltrate, fatigue and improvement in her areas of exposed bone was stated as condition improving and the event bone loss was stated as condition deteriorated. The outcome of the other events was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 15 Aug 2012, 16 Aug 2012 and 17 Aug 2012 inclusive of medical records: patient's date of birth was updated. Patient's family history of adenocarcinoma of lung and concomitant medications Effexor (venlafaxine hydrochloride), Wellbutrin (bupropion), Ativan (lorazepam), Tapazole (thiamazole) and Atenolol were updated. Indication for Aredia and Zometa was updated. Events (depression, hyperthyroidism, severe anxiety, tachycardia, mild proptosis, alcoholism, insomnia, palpitations, Graves 'disease, tremor, leg pain, back pain and salmonella typhi infection, impaired memory, fatigue, ophthalmopathy, thyrotoxicosis, dyslipidemia, bilateral periorbital edema, mild hallux valgus, bursitis, manic episode, bone loss, exposed bone, non-healing, inflammation, bleeding, wound and ulceration in area of tooth # 30) and procedure (stem cell therapy, dental extraction and debridement of # 31) were updated.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 20 Aug 2012 inclusive of medical records. Events were updated: hypothyroidism, plantar calcaneal spur and pneumonia.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 23 Aug 2012 inclusive of medical records. Procedure (removal bone on mandible) and events teeth were loose, plaque, caries control, white spot on the lingual aspect of the 1r molar, pain at injection site and muscle soreness were updated.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 29 Aug 2012 inclusive of medical records. Family history included glaucoma. The events were updated: hypertension (HTN), dry eye syndrome, myopia, astigmatism, presbyopia, nasal septal deviation, keratitis, lid retraction, multiple lytic lesions in the cranium, scarring and fibrosis within the eyelid and ocular hypertension.
Follow up received on 30 Aug 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The event (gastro esophageal reflux disease, slight kidney impairment and anemia) were updated.
Follow-up received on 31 Aug 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Medical history included: Cesarean section. The patient had family history of hypothyroidism. Procedure added: bone marrow transplant. On an unspecified date in 2006 Zometa (zoledronate) was stopped. Event updated: bipolar disorder which was treated with Abilify (aripiprazole) and Klonopin (clonazepam).
Follow-up received on 04 Sep 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Patient's medical history included bone erosion. On an unspecified dated record mentioned that patient had cholecystectomy on an unspecified date. Record dated 01 Aug 2012 stated that the patient had pain in right jaw. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 05 Sep 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Events updated: Trace MR and Trace TR. Lab added: Echocardiogram.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 07 Sep 2012 inclusive of medical records: Event left knee pain, hip pain and plantar fasciitis were updated.
Follow-up received on 11 Sep 2012, via consumer's attorney inclusive of the medical records. Concomitant medications updated (Aspirin, Prilosec, Vivelle). Patient's concurrent condition updated (allergy to augmentin). Procedure updated (hormone replacement therapy, blood transfusion, repair of rectocele, radioactive iodine for hyperthyroidism). Events updated (hot flashes, some vaginal bleeding, rectocele,bloating, severe PMDD, patient felt suicidal, occasional sleep disorder, chronic cervivitis, koilocytosis of squamous cell nucleui with the features of papillomavirus infection and mild squamous epithelial dysplasia/ cervical epithelial neoplasia).
Follow-up received on 17 Sep 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. events updated: nystagmus and hoarseness.
Combined follow-up received on 19 Sep 2012 and 20 Sep 2012, via consumer's attorney inclusive of the medical records. Historical condition updated (renal fistula). Concomitant medications updated (Orthcyclen (ethinylestradiol norgestimate), riseridone, clonazepam). Procedures updated (porta cath, guide-wire assisted esophageal dilation, insertion of peripherally inserted central venous catheter (PICC), porta cath removal). Events updated (dysphagia, barret esophagus, lung infilterate, severe weakness, disorientation, anorexia and muscle cramps and ruptured disc, recent salmonella gastroenteritis, odynophagia and burning left flank pain, dysphagia, barret esophagus, breast tenderness, internal and external haemorroids, generalized colitis, esophagitis, dysfunctions associated with sleep stages or arousal from sleep, bradycardia, gait dysfunction, respiratory distress, snoring/ respiratory abnormality, post nasal drip, low blood pressure typically 90/60, cholelithiasis and extensive cholesterolosis, mild hepatomegaly, cholecystitis and mild gall bladder 0.4 cm polyp, lytic lesions in thoracic spine, lumbar spine, sacrum and iliac bones, venous insufficiency, levoscoliosis and degenerative changes of the thoracic spine, tiny right pleural effusion, osteomyelitis of the jaw, strep throat, chest aching acute, hemoptysis, rigors, marked leukocytosis and sepsis secondary to pneumonia , hyponatremia and hypokalemia, glucose 119 mg/dl).
Follow-up received on 24 Sep 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Procedure (tubal ligation) and event (irregular heart beat) were updated.
Follow up received on 02 Oct 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Procedure (implant placement) and events (mononucleosis & easy bruising) was updated. The outcome was updated for events exposed bone in jaw and bone loss.
Follow up received on 17 Oct 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Events (multiple drug resistant pneumonia and multiple lesions in bones) were updated.
Follow up received on 18 Oct 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Event (psychiatric disorder) was updated.
Follow up received on 31 Oct 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Events (dizziness, nausea, thickening of the gallbladder wall, degenerative disc disease and old anterolateral fracture of the 9th, 10th and 11th ribs) were updated.
Follow-up received on 07 Dec 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Events updated (thyroid orbitopathy and other facial nerve disorder).
Kindly refer PHEH2012US016536.
summary.sendercomment:
MAC: Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments. Treatment dates with Zometa and Aredia are not reported. Some conditions found in the report may not have developed under treatment with the products. The patient's events may be attributable to the underlying malignancy.
Due to constraints of Argus non-serious events of hoarsness [dysphonia, NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa:], Hot flashes [hot flush, NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa: UL/UL/UL], sleep disorder[NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa: UL/UL/UL], abdominal distention[NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa: UL/UL/UL], left knee pain/hip pain [arthralgia, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa: L/L/L], sleep disorder NOS [sleep disorder, NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa: UL/UL/UL], fatigue[fatigue, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa: L/L/L] , anemia[anemia, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa: L/L/L], back pain[back pain, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa: L/L/L], leg pain[pain in extremity, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa: L/L/L], palpitations [NS, Aredia: UL/UL, Zometa: UL/UL/UL], insomnia[insomnia, NS, Aredia: L/L, Zometa:L/L/L] are deleted from event tab and placed in admin notes.
